summary: Oh look, it’s me again with a plan that I’m probably not going to stick to. Starting Thursday: - no ice cream - no bread - no...
body:
Oh look, it’s me again with a plan that I’m probably not going to stick to.

Starting Thursday:

- no ice cream
- no bread
- no pop/soda
- no alcohol
- no chips/french fries
- no pizza/junk food

Fasting from 8pm to 12pm with no cheating! 

Going to try it for a month. It’s going to be damn hard.
Will make notes on my weight, mood, energy levels, sleep quality, skin etc. 

I’ve always kept to the idea that a little bit of bad won’t hurt, but I’m terrible with controlling it then. It isn’t just ‘this one small treat’, it ends up being multiple things and then I’ve ruined any good eating that day. 

Wish me luck! I’m really determined this time. I just want change.

title: Baltimore Ravens vs. Tennessee Titans Prediction and Preview https://ift.tt/eA8V8J
description:
The Tennessee Titans and the Baltimore Ravens are both trying to recover from lousy Week 5 offensive performances in which neither team scored a touchdown and lost to inferior opponents on the road.

Tennessee’s 13-12 loss to Buffalo last week, as embarrassing as it was, still allowed the Titans to sit in a two-way tie for first place in the AFC South at 3-2. The beauty of a bad division, I suppose.

summary: when to breath in and breath out and accessories about Phraks GSLP via /r/Fitness
title: when to breath in and breath out and accessories about Phraks GSLP via /r/Fitness
body:
and through Mouth or Nose(while doing exercises)?

I am novelty guy. I picked up phraks greyskull LP from sidebar

Phraks GSLP in image form

I don’t know when to breath out and breath in and through nose or mouth (while doing OHP, DL, Bench Press, chinups, Barbell row say whatever exercises in PGSLP. Does it have considerable impact over lifting?

Also, I am thinking of adding few accessories exercises. Currently I am doing everything with barbel only (OHP, DL ,BP..so on)

My forearms are very weak wrist and grip are also weak. Forearms look very small.

I was thinking if adding forearm exercises and farmer walk plus Latpulldown.

As I am unable to do pull ups..Not even one. So came to know through you tube videos that I need work on brachia radialis muscles. (forearm muscle) (also negative pull ups) so it will help me in pull ups.So was thinking of adding forearm curl to work on that muscle.

So, My question is do I need to add(do) accessories only on particular day like ‘do forearms accessories only on bench day and not on day when you have DL or something like this.’ It was just example. Or I can do accessories on lifting days that is on M-W-R irrespective of which lifts (DL,OHP,BP so on ) comes on that day.

In case it matters: 25 Male/135 lbs/5'5 Priority: anesthetics

Thank you.

summary: How much is too much? via /r/Fitness
title: How much is too much? via /r/Fitness
body:
Having issues fitting in workouts with my schedule… As a result I am looking at trying to wake up and work out at 5am-7am M-F. The biggest issue is if I work out at 5 am, I typically go (almost nonstop, between classes and work) until ether 9:30pm at night, or 11pm (depending on if its a day with late classes or late work).

If I do this I am able to kinda squeeze in anywhere from 6 hours to 8 hours of sleep a night. Is this viable? I’m thinking about just waking up, downing some preworkout, amd hitting the gym. Figure the caffine and morning workouts would keep me up and energized through the rest of the day… Thoughts?
